DoosuurIwambe, Abuja The Federal Government has approved the appointment of Dr. Obinna Onodugo as the New Chief Medical Director (CMD), University of Nigeria Teaching Hospital, Enugu State. The Appointment is for an initial term of four years with effect from 14th May 2019. Congratulating Dr Onodugo on his new appointment, the Minister of Health, Prof. Isaac Adewole reminded him of the enormous responsibilities of his office and the yearnings of Nigerians for an effective and responsive healthcare delivery system. Adewole further advised the new CMD to justify the confidence reposed in him by President Mohhamadu Buhari. He also advised him to collaborate with all stakeholders to ensure industrial harmony in the Health Sector.